"Could this possibly be a human... arm?"\n<Yukine>\F[15]

September 4th, at last, I was able to save enough
money to buy my home. I was lucky to find a
property at a bargain price. Now I can give my
eight-year-old Shizuka her own room.

October 27th, the move is finished. The inside is
surprisingly spacious, more so than the exterior
suggests. If it were a detached house with a
garden in Tokyo, it would be something to boast
about.

I've put my wife through some trouble with the
noise in the neighborhood, but this place is
astonishingly quiet. Even when my daughter runs up
the stairs, you can't hear a sound. By the way,
there wasn't supposed to be a Japanese-style
storehouse in the garden, was there?

October 28th, Shizuka has been acting strange
since we moved in. She says there's someone in the
house and garden. That can't be possible.

Only I, my wife Kana, and Shizuka should be living
in this house. It must be her imagination.

October 29th, Mr. Suzuki from next door came over
for dinner. Kana's cooking is the best. The liver
especially is delicious. It's my first time eating
raw human organs, but they're fatty and tasty.

It's just too bad that I won't be able to eat the
meat and potatoes we got as a share ever again.

October 30th, a hatchet arrived by courier. When I
tried it out on the delivery man, it split him
open like a watermelon.

It was a good purchase. Kana wanted to try it too,
and when I lent it to her, she cut off her own
wrist. Looks like I'll be making dinner tonight.

November 2nd, there are a lot of police officers
outside. It's my first time seeing something
called SAT. It seems they want to enter the house.

Since it's such a special occasion, I think I'll
throw a party and celebrate grandly with cake.

Inviting them over after dividing Kana and Shizuka
into smaller pieces and putting them in the fridge
might have been a mistake. I hope they suit the
taste of the police officers.

(It's a pretty tight hole... but with some effort,
I might be able to get through.)
(Can I make it back to the entrance from here...)

"Huh, it won't turn on? Maybe it's missing
batteries?"\n<Yukine>

(It doesn't look like I can go any further. I
should head back.)

May 16th, a lingering spirit. Two exorcism ritual
items damaged. August 15th, failed to return. One
exorcism ritual item damaged.

September 2nd, an evil spirit. Three exorcism
ritual items damaged. October 30th, an evil
spirit. Two banishment ritual items damaged.

November 3rd, an evil spirit. Three exorcism
ritual items damaged. January 10th, twenty-eight
ritual items damaged.

The remaining item is hidden inside the house. I
pray that the light will be of help to someone.

(Eh... Why is there a place like this inside the
mansion?)

(The interior of the house is new... but the
unpleasant atmosphere is getting thicker.)

"This ghost... what should I do... It's completely
turned into an evil spirit... contaminated by a
curse."\n<Yukine>\F[15]

(If it catches me... I'll surely be killed. I have
to run away!)\F[15]
